cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper discusses data-driven methods for analyzing and processing 3D shapes, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for shape classification, segmentation, matching, and reconstruction, as well as graphics (cs.GR) techniques for modeling, visualization, and exploration. The use of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also mentioned as a key feature of data-driven approaches. Finally, the paper touches on scene analysis and synthesis, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
